Merge pull request #189 from DigitalNZ/pm/fix-dates Date.current and Date.today are not using UTC...

Date.current and Date.today are not using UTC... if you are in NZT which is 12 hours ahead of UTC and do something like this:
Date.today < MyObject.created_at.utc.to_date
Date.today would be 2019-03-02 because it's using NZT but created_at will be
2019-03-01 and we don't get the result we expect.

So the idea is to avoid to use the Date object
